1. Alport syndrome
2. Loeys-Dietz syndrome
3. Marfan syndrome
4. Ehlers-Danlos syndrome (vascular or classic type)
5. Usher syndrome (type II)
6. Autosomal dominant polycystic kidney disease (ADPKD)
7. Osteogenesis imperfecta
8. Williams-Beuren syndrome
9. Jervell and Lange-Nielsen syndrome
10. Branchio-oto-renal (BOR) syndrome

Each of these conditions can present with a combination of the symptoms and clinical features described in the patient's phenotype. It is important to note that further clinical, genetic, and possibly imaging studies would be necessary to confirm any of these diagnoses.
